cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as salient object segmentation, edge detection, and skeleton extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a unified architecture for solving these tasks, which involves deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on multiple datasets, which could also make it relevant to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
